CSS RULESET/RULE or "CSS Syntax" is composed of selector and a declaration block.

â€¢ Selector or group of selector -  are the entire elements
â€¢ Declaration Block - the main function of elements
â€¢ Declaration - these are the value inside the Declaration Block
it has a semicolon at the end of statement

â€¢ CSS Declaration is composed of Property Separator and Value
e.g.
___
background-color : lightblue;
___
â€¢ background-color - property
â€¢ : - separator
â€¢ lightblue - value
___
â€¢ Property - human readable identifier indicates which stylistic features to change.
â€¢ Value - given to a property, specific style should he changed
